HEADWORD: Episcopal
<hw>E*pis"co*pal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>episcopalis</ets>, fr. <ets>episcopus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧piscopal</ets>. See <er>Bishop</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Governed by bishops; <as>as, an <ex>episcopal</ex>
church</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Belonging to, or vested in, bishops; <as>as,
<ex>episcopal</ex> jurisdiction or authority; the <ex>episcopal</ex>
system.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Episcopalian</ent>⟦br⟧
